            <term xml:id="term-k000276-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">zhengji</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000276-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">正脊</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000276-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">正脊</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000276-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">zhèngjǐ</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000276-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">cheng-chi</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000276-6" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000276-1" type="literal_translation">main ridge (lit.)</term>
            <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000276</idno>
            <note type="Note">
               <p>under construction</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">Literally meaning “main spine,” zhengji 正脊 refers to a type of roof ridge  <term ref="/keyword/k000275">(wuji 屋脊)</term>. It runs parallel to the width of the building at the intersection of 
                  the front and rear slopes of the roof. The term was first documented in Yingzao fashi, and its meaning has remained stable over time.</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant">“正脊”為中國古代建築中屋脊的一種，指屋頂前後兩坡交接處與面闊平行的脊，首次見於《營造法式》（李 2009,13.3a），並沿用至今。</p>
            </note>
